ed motivic cohomology theory is stably birational invariant on smooth\nproper $k$-schemes of finite type (resp. smooth $k$-schemes of finite type). In\nthe course of constructing $S_{sb},$ we have also shown a general local\nuniformization theorem of the first kind for arbitrary geometric valuations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Oct 2022 20:07:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 28 Oct 2022 14:55:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-10-31"}
